# Shell scripts run only under Linux (the Emscripten toolchain). Checked out
# with CRLF on Windows they fail in a way that is genuinely hard to diagnose:
# /bin/sh reads the trailing \r as part of the shebang, reports nothing useful,
# and the script's side effects simply never happen.
*.sh text eol=lf
Makefile text eol=lf

# Generated, but tracked so the npm package builds without a Rust toolchain.
# linguist-generated keeps it out of diffs and language stats.
#
# eol=lf is load-bearing: CI regenerates these on Linux and fails the build if
# `git diff` shows a change. Without a pinned line ending, a checkout on Windows
# converts them to CRLF and the drift check fails on line endings alone — a
# false alarm that says "your types are stale" when they are identical.
packages/tex-engine/src/generated/** linguist-generated=true text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never diff or line-ending-convert these.
*.wasm binary
*.fmt binary
*.pdf binary
*.tfm binary
*.pfb binary
*.otf binary
*.ttf binary
